cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper discusses the use of synthetic data for training deep networks in computer vision tasks such as stereo and optical flow estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the creation of training data, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
